    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-03-05T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-03-05T18:00:00-05:00" n="717"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d717">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 652.119/605</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_PWH1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Page</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-03-05T18:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 5, 1918, 6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>6772. Following telegram, dated March 2, has been received by the Department from
                    the American Ambassador at Madrid: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>French Embassy requests Department be informed that matter of Spanish
                            exterior <hi rend="italic">rentes</hi> in which Spanish Government is
                            much interested, is being withheld from French-Spanish agreement and for
                            future consideration in connection with English credit. Embassy approved
                            of this course and is strongly of opinion that French-Spanish agreement
                            will be irretrievably lost if question of English credit is injected
                            therein. Embassy stands ready to ratify Spanish-American agreement as
                            modified by Department’s 914, February 26, 8 p.m.<note n="1"
                                xml:id="d717fn1">Not printed.</note> English are apparently desirous
                            to delay ratification and to reopen negotiations.</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>Department has been advised by the French representatives here that the
                    French-Spanish agreement has been ready for signature by the Spanish Prime
                    Minister since February 28.</p>
                <p>Department wishes you to make representations to the British Government to the
                    effect that this Government considers it highly desirable that ratification of
                    the French-Spanish and Spanish-American agreements be no longer delayed. Please
                    report at once by cable result of your representations.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_PFL1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Polk</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
